        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I trying to migrate from 1.8.4 to 1.9.7, but the ldap adapter is not working.\r\nI tried with multiple versions, version 1.9.2 -1.9.7 failed.\r\nOnly version 1.9.1 worked.\r\n\r\nI get invalid credentials error.\r\nAfter debuging I get this exception\r\nZend_Ldap_Exception: 0xa (Referral; 0000202B: RefErr: DSID-0310063C, data 0, 1 access points ref 1: 'XXXXX.net' ): No object found for: (&(objectClass=user)(sAMAccountName=USERNAME)) in C:\\Files\\Apps\\PHP\\ZendFramework-1.9.2\\library\\Zend\\Ldap.php on line 653\r\nIt seems that bug was introduced in version 1.9.2.\r\n\r\nHere is my configuration\r\nldap.server1.host = XXXXXX.na.XXXXX.net\r\nldap.server1.useSsl = false\r\nldap.server1.accountDomainName = na.XXXXX.net\r\nldap.server1.accountDomainNameShort = DDDDD\r\nldap.server1.accountCanonicalForm = 4\r\nldap.server1.baseDn = \"CN=na,DC=XXXXX,DC=net\"\r\n\r\nThe following used to work\r\n\r\nZend_Loader::loadClass('Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap');\r\n$config = Zend_Registry::get('config');\r\n$ldap_options = $config->ldap->toArray();\t\t        \r\n$ldap_adapter = new Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap($ldap_options, $username, $password);\r\n\r\n\/\/ attempt to authenticate\r\n$auth = Zend_Auth::getInstance();\r\n$ldap_result = $auth->authenticate($ldap_adapter);\r\nif ( $ldap_result->isValid() ) {\r\n\techo \"In\";\r\n} else {\r\n\techo \"Out\";\r\n}"
        },
