                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38062",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=valter",
                        "name": "valter",
                        "displayName": "Valter Kungla",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think it is not related to this bug because version change 1.9.1 din't help me. Also I have a different messaga \"getting first entry\"\r\nI don't have any idea of that and google seems to be empty too...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=valter",
                        "name": "valter",
                        "displayName": "Valter Kungla",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-27T05:36:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-27T05:36:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38374",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You're right, it may be possible that this problem was introduced with 1.9.2 when we added group membership features.\r\n\r\nAfter I cleanup this piece of code it might be possible that this issue is also resolved with r21008 in trunk and r21009 in 1.10-release branch. \r\n\r\nPerhaps you can give it a try.\r\n\r\nAltogether it's quite hard to debug such issues without having access to the exact same environment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-09T06:19:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-09T06:19:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
                        "displayName": "Timo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have the same problem. \r\nUsing version 1.9.2 the Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap login worked fine.\r\nI did not change my code but with version 1.9.7 or 1.10.1 the Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap login does not work anymore and I don't know why. So I have to downgrade my application to version 1.9.2 what gets me into other trouble... :-( Any ideas?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
                        "displayName": "Timo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-17T01:20:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-17T01:20:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Timo,\r\n\r\nsame thing. Most likely this issue has been fixed with r21008 in trunk and r21009 in 1.10-release branch. But the commit to the release-branch was too late to make it into 1.10.1.\r\nYou therefore must wait for 1.10.2 or use a direct checkout from the trunk or the 1.10-release-branch.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\n\r\nStefan",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-17T03:52:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-17T03:52:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38509",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
                        "displayName": "Timo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ok, I fixed my problem by adding the fields username and password to my ldap server options array. I did not use those values before. Now this is necessary because of the empty bind $ldap->bind(); in Auth\\Adapter\\Ldap.php on Line 323 (V 1.10.1). For username and password I use the same values which the user entered for login. this works for me.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
                        "displayName": "Timo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-17T03:55:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-17T03:55:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38510",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nice work-around... Your observation is cortrect.\r\nAs I mentioned above, this whole thing should be fixed with 1.10.2",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-17T04:00:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-17T04:00:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38511",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
                        "displayName": "Timo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Stefan,\r\nThanks for your feedback. So I will be waiting for 1.10.2 ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=worschtebrot",
                        "name": "worschtebrot",
